      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CHE OLE (4) has been about the money at all four runs this prep. Had a seven-week let-up before closing well to finish third last start over 1300m at this track. Strips fitter and looks ready for a first run beyond 1400m. SIRIUS MOSS (8) made it three minor placings on the trot when she raced handy then boxed on fairly to finish third over 1750m at Muswellbrook last time out. Back in trip but the blinkers going on will sharpen her up. Looks a genuine threat. ORANGE TSUNAMI (3) progressed nicely at his latest outing when second-up from a spell, battling on for third over 1350m at Wyong. Looks ready to tackle this longer journey. PROXIMA CENTAURI (6) didn't do a bad job first-up over 1300m here when friendless in betting. Back in better order this prep so might be worth following. SHE CAN SALSA (7) mixes her form but should benefit from the addition of blinkers this afternoon.",
